# Customer Purchase Intent Prediction

## Overview

This project predicts whether an online customer is likely to complete a purchase based on browsing behavior using machine learning.

## Objectives

- Clean and preprocess customer behavior data
- Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Engineer meaningful features
- Train multiple classification models
- Compare model performance
- Perform hyperparameter tuning
- Identify important features
- Save the best model
- Generate predictions

## Dataset

Online Shoppers Purchasing Intention Dataset

Features include:
- Administrative
- Informational
- ProductRelated
- BounceRates
- ExitRates
- PageValues
- Month
- VisitorType
- Weekend

Target:
- Revenue

## Models Used

- Logistic Regression
- Decision Tree
- Random Forest
- Gradient Boosting

## Evaluation Metrics

- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- F1 Score
- ROC-AUC
- Confusion Matrix

## Technologies

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Scikit-learn
- Joblib

## Results

Random Forest produced the best performance after hyperparameter tuning.

The trained model was saved using Joblib and predictions were exported as a CSV file.

